as far as them being at each others throats, who knows, this is all some type of internet popularity contest anyhow. its like some people have this need to be famous, or infamous.

Video is average CAM quality, ie..not great...what one would expect for a CAM.

Audio, on the other hand is terrible.  After 10 minutes, I stopped watching, because I could not understand one word, not one.  It sounds like you are listening to it through a tube.  More closely would be that the whole movie sounds like the teachers in the Charlie Brown TV shows.  That and the added bonus of what sounded like EVERYONE in the movie theater talking. Really, it was that bad.  Anyone else who says differently is candy coating it.

So, while video is watchable, audio is the worst I have ever experienced.

Oh, and so you know my setup, my computer is hooked up to my Onkyo HT Receiver through HDMI and then HDMI from that to my TV, and I use VLC player.  It's the same when trying to just watch on the computer as well.
